65.2	The_Accidental_Billionaires	The Accidental Billionaires	The Accidental Billionaires: The Founding of Facebook, A Tale of Sex, Money, Genius, and Betrayal is a 2009 book by Ben Mezrich about the founding of Facebook. Co-founder Eduardo Saverin served as Mezrich's main consultant. Mark Zuckerberg declined to speak with Ben Mezrich while the book was being researched and after Zuckerberg and Saverin settled their lawsuit, Saverin broke off contact with the author.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/07/The_Accidental_Billionaires.jpg/230px-The_Accidental_Billionaires.jpg
